Question 1) What is HashMap?
Answer) The HashMap class of the Java collection framework provide the functionality of the hashtable data structure.
        Hashmap class implements the map interface which allows us to store key and value pairs, where key should be always
        unique. If you try to insert duplicate value, it will override the value.
        It is easy to perform operation using the key index like updation or insertion and deletion etc.

*** Points to remember
1) Java Hashmap contain value based on the key.
2) Java Hashmap contain only unique keys.
3) Java Hashmap may have one null key and multiple null values.
4) Java Hashmap is non synchronized.
5) Java Hashmap maintain no order.
6) The intial default capacity of Java hashmap class is 16 with a load factor of 0.75.